## What Has Been Done (Implementation Details)

**Discover feed**  
• Non-functional search bar removed; feed uses full width.  
• Map entry: single floating teal pill (map icon) bottom-right; feed extends to bottom of screen (no gray/white box).  
• Map pill hidden when any detail view is shown (event, spot, or collection).  
• Feed list and background use bottom safe area so content goes all the way down.

**Save (Flow 1)**  
• Unified save control: small gray capsule, bookmark icon + save count; teal when saved. Same style on cards and detail screens.  
• Save works from: event cards, spot cards, map event preview, event detail (hero), spot detail (hero), collection detail (hero), and individual spot rows in a collection.  
• Save count updates in place after toggle (events, spots, collection spots); backend save/unsave wired.

**First-run / location**  
• App prompts for location; if denied or unavailable, fallback is Stockholm (not Manhattan). AppConfig fallbackLatitude/Longitude for Stockholm.

**Map view**  
• Full screen height; filter row is floating card; spacing so arrow/recenter not cramped.  
• Close (X) removed; Discover pill (compass) bottom-right dismisses map.  
• Event preview save button uses same capsule style and updates count.

**Detail pages**  
• Event: single save pill on hero; "FRIENDS WHO SAVED THIS" with mutuals row; no second save in body.  
• Spot: single save pill on hero; no second save in body; state/count from feed when opened from Discover.  
• Collection: "Collection" label removed; spot cards in "PLACES IN THIS COLLECTION" do not show number badges (by design — no amber/orange 1, 2, 3… on cards); tags only from discover categories; save on collection and on each spot row wired to API.

