## UI Sweep for Consistency and Quality (Before Release)

**Required:** Run a full UI/UX sweep so the alpha feels consistent and polished. Every surface should be checked for alignment with the design system and for quality of interaction.

**Checklist:**

• **Save button** — Same capsule style (gray → teal when saved, bookmark + count) everywhere it appears.  
• **Typography, spacing, colors** — Consistent across Discover, Map, Profile, and creation flows (portal primary, muted, cards, section labels).  
• **Detail screens** — No duplicate actions; single save control where redundancy was removed; mutuals/avatars where specified.  
• **List and scroll** — No stray gray/white bars; content and background extend to edges and safe areas.  
• **Map** — Floating controls (filters, Discover pill) clearly tappable and not overlapping content.  
• **Creation flows** — Event (and later spot) creation: clear labels, sensible order, validation and error states, consistent with rest of app.  
• **Empty and error states** — Helpful copy and visuals where lists or content are empty or fail to load.  
• **Accessibility** — Labels and identifiers in place; verify VoiceOver and dynamic type where relevant.

